but Madame said if
a new Degawa Girl joins,

47
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:58,520
- one old girl can go.
- Yes.

48
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:01,080
If we get one new student,
one should graduate.

49
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,400
New student...

50
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:06,520
We must let them graduate.

51
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:10,600
At first, Degawa Girls were young,
I thought it was nice and new,

52
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:14,240
but when the two young girls joined,
they suddenly looked old.

53
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,320
It's not fresh at all.

54
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,280
We're young! We're very young!

55
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:22,480
Yokota, it's the first time
you joined, right?

56
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,040
- Yes.
- How was it?

57
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,480
I had a lot of fun.

58
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:29,600
I went to steal the skills
of the older girls.

59
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,800
"Older girls..."

60
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:35,160
The three old girls
are in white costumes here.

61
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:38,640
It's not white costume!

62
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,960
Why? Why?

63
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:43,640
Like they're prepared to die
to do something.

64
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,720
It's fresh!

65
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,360
Saga!

66
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,800
Impressive!

67
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:51,560
Ow... hot...

68
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:52,720
It's difficult.

69
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,480
Rock, paper, scissors.

70
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,200
Ms Kawakita, do it again.

71
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,480
- "Yay!"
- It's horrible!

72
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:01,920
"Degawa Girls' Gathering
in Saga, Oita"

73
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,960
900 kilometres from Tokyo,

74
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:07,800
two new girls will also join.

75
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:12,200
Degawa Girls' Gathering
in Saga, Oita.

76
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,720
We've come to...

77
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,280
Saga!

78
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,480
This is Saga Castle History Museum.

79
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:23,840
The first iron cannon in Japan
was manufactured here,

80
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:27,440
it's also known to have led
the Meiji Restoration.

81
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:30,400
Madame, we have
another new Degawa Girl join--

82
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,560
Dewi Girls.

83
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,640
Yes, Dewi Girls.

84
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,160
Yokota, introduce yourself.

85
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:36,160
I'm Mayuu Yokota, nice to meet you.

86
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,560
I'm 21 years old.
Please call me Yokota.

87
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:40,440
- Okay.
- Nice to meet you.

88
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,080
- Did you apply for it?
- She's not interested!

89
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:45,120
I went to the same audition
with Yumeppe.

90
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,960
That means you were the first place
and you were the second place?

91
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:48,920
"1st place, 2nd place"

92
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,600
We were supposed to join together.

93
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,880
Don't make things awkward!

94
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,600
- Why do you stand like this anyway?
- No idea.

95
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:58,520
But somehow it feels like
the two of them were demoted.

96
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,800
That's so mean!

97
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:02,440
Let's start
the Degawa Girls Gathering.

98
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:05,560
First, it's the glass art
Madame would like to do.

99
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,040
It's said that
glass was first introduced to Japan

100
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,960
in the Yayoi period,

101
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:14,400
but manufacturing of glassware
started in the Edo period,

102
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,360
in full swing.

103
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:18,360
This time, they'll learn it
at Soejima Glassware,

104
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,840
which was founded in 1903.

105
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,440
Who will teach us?

106
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:23,400
It's him.

107
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:24,840
- Oh, he's our teacher?
- Yes.

108
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,480
What about you, sir?

109
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,440
I'm only going to watch.

110
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:29,680
Only watch?

111
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:31,680
Oh? Are you from the neighbourhood?

112
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,400
- The company's president, right?
- What?

113
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,960
He doesn't look like a president.

114
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:39,000
He totally does! His skin is fair.

115
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,840
What kind of glassware do you make?

116
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:44,000
It's called Hizen Vidro,

117
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:47,120
it's Saga's traditional glassware.

118
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:51,640
Saga's important intangible
cultural asset, Hizen Vidro.

119
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:55,280
"Vidro" means "glass" in Portuguese.

120
00:04:55,800 --> 00:05:00,560
It is made by glassblowing,
without using any mould.

121
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,640
To shape the glassware,

122
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:05,440
crafters use gravitational force
and centrifugal force well.

123
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,760
It is difficult,

124
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:10,000
but no two pieces of glassware
are the same.

125
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:14,280
It's made into glassware that has
a warmth unique to handmade work.

126
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,920
This time, they'll learn from
the teacher for two days,

127
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,360
and make their own unique glassware.

128
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:24,240
Madame will make a champagne glass.

129
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:27,800
Now this part of a champagne glass
is narrower,

130
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:30,000
it's become the mainstream.

131
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,560
On the other hand,
the youngest Yumeppe...

132
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,280
Like this.

133
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,400
I'll make a vase for my grandma.

134
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,480
How wonderful that is!

135
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,640
- My grandma loves flowers.
- What, Ms Kawakita?

136
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:43,520
- I'll make a glass for my grandma.
- Shut up!

137
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,440
Stop it!

138
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,960
And Degawa...

139
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,560
What's that?

140
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:51,000
- Liar!
- I'm scared!

141
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,800
You've never bought your wife
souvenirs,

142
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:55,520
why do you do this?

143
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,280
This isn't right!

144
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,640
Day one is the beginner's course.

145
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:04,800
No matter what glassware it is,
the first thing they do is Tamatori.

146
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,960
The glass is melted into
a syrupy-state in the furnace,

147
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,880
it's rolled around
the tip of a stick.

148
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,920
The small ball has a diameter
of three centimetres.

149
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:18,160
Blow air into it little by little,

150
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:20,400
and the ball that forms the base
is done.

151
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,120
This is the core.

152
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,360
We'll put another layer of glass
on top,

153
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,160
and make it expand.

154
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:29,240
Madame tries it first.

155
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:32,160
Can she wrap a small ball around it,
like the teacher?

156
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,720
Madame, isn't it fast?

157
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,400
She secured 10 times the amount
of the teacher's.

158
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:42,160
She blows air into it,
but it doesn't' move at all.

159
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,200
It's difficult.

160
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,560
Actually, this looks easy,

161
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:49,240
but it takes three years
to master the skill.

162
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,200
Good...

163
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,720
Degawa is doing it quite well.

164
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,840
He'll shape the glass now.

165
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,280
Turn it...

166
00:06:58,960 --> 00:06:59,880
Good!

167
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:02,440
- Good...
- Ow... hot...

168
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,560
- Good...
- Wow!

169
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,200
It's hot!

170
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:06,320
Compete with time.

171
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:08,280
- Hurry, hurry!
- Hurry up!

172
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,240
You can't do it at all.

173
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,280
He didn't make that sound.

174
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,800
Anyway, I was surprised!

175
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:18,400
This isn't hot at all.

176
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,440
But you said it was hot.

177
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:21,880
To make it expand,

178
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:24,760
they need to wrap the glass
around the part

179
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:27,160
further from the tip,
like the teacher did.

180
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,080
Yumeppe showed the difference.

181
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,960
- Wow!
- Yumeppe!

182
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:37,160
New girl Yokota successfully
expanded it.

183
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,600
I made it!

184
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,960
Our new Degawa Girls are amazing!

185
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,680
What is it?
Maybe their breaths are fresher?

186
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:51,880
All the members still need practise,

187
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:54,920
so we'll show you the craftsman's
wonderful techniques.

188
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,800
The glass expands to the ideal size,

189
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,800
it's moved to another stick,

190
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,760
and it's cut away
from the original stick.

191
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:02,840
It's difficult.

192
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:07,160
The hole opened here will become
the mouth of the cup or the glass.

193
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:11,840
Expand it according to what
you want to make, and it's done.

194
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,640
In the case of making a plate...

195
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,720
It's impressive.

196
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:20,840
Centrifugal force.

197
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,840
It's finished by using
centrifugal force,

198
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,680
and this is the finished glass art.

199
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:30,040
The thing that can only be made
using the technique here in Japan

200
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:32,560
is this blue saké warmer.

201
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:37,040
It is done by using two sticks
together at the same time.

202
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:39,960
Blow into one stick,

203
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:42,840
and stretch the part of the mouth
using the other stick.

204
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,960
- That's difficult.
- Wow!

205
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,880
It doesn't break?

206
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:52,600
When the glass sets,
use gravitational force to shape it.

207
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:53,800
In Japan,

208
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:56,760
it's a traditional technique that's
only passed down in Hizen Vidor.

209
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,320
At the same time, the amateurs...

210
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,760
He's so noisy.

211
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:05,160
Wow, it isn't hot at all.

212
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:07,200
What was that, then?

213
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:11,240
The teacher's wife
is a rather good teacher.

214
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,960
She lets him do a little,

215
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:15,120
but basically, she does it together.

216
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,600
On the other hand,
Mr Fujii is a craftsman,

217
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:20,800
he never spoils his students.

218
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,720
That's how far it can get.
Mr Fujii, have a look.

219
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,120
Take it out.

220
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,760
- How is it?
- Hurry up.

221
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,960
It'd take 10 minutes to finish
if he helps,

222
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:30,680
but she spent 50 whole minutes

223
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:33,200
to heat and mould the glass,
repeatedly.

224
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,280
Her face is already oily.

225
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,320
He doesn't change
his educational principle

226
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,600
for Madame, either.

227
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:46,800
You dropped it with a thump.

228
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:53,480
We aren't going to become experts
of glass art.

229
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,600
Among them, the talented one
is new girl Yokota.

230
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:01,640
Only a few people can be this good.

231
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:04,800
The way she spins the stick
is logical.

232
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,560
The president suddenly appeared,

233
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:09,040
and praised the way
she turns the stick.

234
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:13,240
It is turned stably,
so gravitational force acts equally,

235
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,440
and it's kept as a beautiful sphere.

236
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,600
I have potential.

237
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:19,280
She has potential? Teacher!

238
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,360
She has potential.

239
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:23,960
You never said that to me!
I turned it 30--

240
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,320
On the other hand,
the one who has no talent

241
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,680
but made her presence felt,
is old girl Tani.

242
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,240
- It's hot!
- Oh, watch out!

243
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:32,160
Stop it!

244
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,880
Self-claimed burn.

245
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:38,600
Four people are looking after you
for your burn. What the heck?

246
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,720
Hey, Maria!

247
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:42,840
It hurts!

248
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:46,640
It's a tiny burn and you need
four adults to look after you?

249
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:47,560
It hurts!

250
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:48,760
Are you okay with that?

251
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,640
And Yumeppe...

252
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:54,040
She doesn't think about
being filmed at all,

253
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:56,840
and she's making effort
for her grandma...

254
00:10:57,040 --> 00:11:00,920
That's the look on her face when she
makes something for her grandma.

255
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:04,600
But Yumeppe is also thinking
about various things.

256
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,000
Is there anything you want to learn
from the senior girls?

257
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,960
Like their reaction,

258
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:11,600
the way they fawn on the crew.

259
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:16,720
I mean Maria's burn
was nothing serious, right?

260
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,680
That's what I think,

